<br>
Protestors: I am totally sick and tired of these smelly, moccasin and beret wearing, coffee house vermin. Someone once told me that when stupid people are misinformed, idiotic hijinx follow. Protestors are demonstrative of this being a valid statement. By protestors I am focusing on those preaching against democratic government and trying to return &quot;humanity&quot; to the people. Industrial disputes..well...I can look past that. But it is the former that really @#%$ me. They run around with their banners and pathetic rhymes based on what? Filtered, second hand information, that's what! They assume they have somehow had knowledge bestowed upon them which surpasses that of professionals, officials, statesmen...security agencies. For example, in Australia at the moment ASIO, our spooks, have been apprehending and investigating suspected terrorists. Under government law they have been permitted unwarranted entry into these houses. So...what is wrong with this you say? Well...nothing...they are apprehending people that have the potential to cause the deaths of hundreds...but is the Australian public satisfied? NO! We have had weak minded little fools claiming to be humanitarians yelling &quot;these people have rights too!&quot; Implying that 1. We should tell suspects we are coming to investigate them. 2. We should ring the doorbell. Does anyone see the flaw in this reasoning...because I seem to be in a minority when I say 'yes'. Oh, and the media interviewed a suspect's daughter and she says, &quot;They broke down the door and had guns and black uniforms!&quot; and a tear flows from her eye. Well NEWSFLASH miss, it's your father that put you in that mess, not the government. <br>
<br>
2. Uni-students. What can I say about uni-students. I can say that when I become one I am going to be thoroughly ashamed of my peers, that's what I can say alright. Yesterday a group of uni students burned an Australian flag and an American flag...these students are Australian by the way. Any reprecussions? Nope...Why? Because they are students. Now what should have happened is that they be charged with treason and deported to one of the many countries where they share solidarity with the downtrodden...maybe the pygmy people of Peru, or the disgruntled steel workers of Lesotho's seedier parts. Also they like using the phrase &quot;stop the racist war&quot;....yet they are desacrating the symbols of nations...hmm...well done socialist alliance, you have screwed up again.<br>
<br>
*breathes* Well...hmm...just needed to vent. No doubt there is a puffed up, civic-minded university fool visiting these parts, so go ahead...strike back...astonish us with your general knowledge. <p> zzzaaaap! </p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=simonm5>SimonM5</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0> at: 10/31/02 8:40:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kennygeeze>Kenny Geeze</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/31/02 4:46:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11368.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.lespaul.com/menu1/deluxe.jpg width=080 height=110></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Becoming A Fascist...by Simon M5</span><hr size=1> And that's exactly why they should create flags filled with high explosives. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=darkstalker1>DarkStalker1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/31/02 7:37:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11368.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~ceg007/_uimages/Ds1copy.JPG  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Becoming A Fascist...by Simon M5</span><hr size=1> And I  Thought this sort of Sh!t only happened in America <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=otakulad>OtakuLad</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Canadian <img src=http://contest.polykarbon.com/badge1.gif></span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/31/02 8:09:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11368.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.calgarymedia.com/asuka.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Becoming A Fascist...by Simon M5</span><hr size=1> Nah, they burn American flags in the Middle East every day.<br>
Actually, flag burning is very disrespectful, but in the grand scheme of things, there are worse things.<br>
<br>
Personal privacy and freedoms are going to take a heck of a beating. It's unfortunate, but the price of freedom is eternal vigilance, both externally and internally. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=simonm5>SimonM5</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(10/31/02 8:47:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11368.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/simonx/avatar.jpg width=79 height=108></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Becoming A Fascist...by Simon M5</span><hr size=1> Well I have always valued living in Australia. Everything that happens here is pretty tame compared to what happens in the rest of the world. I mean, for the last week our main news topic has been the dropping of Mark Waugh from test cricket. Personally, that is just fine with me. I feel safe and secure...happy...starting to get a bit hot (:P summer) And it really shits me that these good for nothing little assholes can never be satisfied. I wouldn't at all be sad or disheartened if the government announced a ban on student rallies...call me a Nazi...but at least we wouldn't have to put up with their misinformed shenanigans. <p> zzzaaaap! </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scorp10n>Scorp10n</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/1/02 2:26:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11368.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://distopia.net/ppic/knob.jpg height=84 width=125></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Becoming A Fascist...by Simon M5</span><hr size=1> I can burn a flag if I want. I could get your photo and burn it, piss on it, spit on it, defecate on it, whatever, and you couldn't do anything about it! It's rather similar - in both cases, a party is demeaned/offended - but you'll survive, won't you? Charging someone with treason because they burned a flag? You ARE a fascist. Laws are (supposed) to be created for the benefit of the people they affect - burning a flag hurts no one at all, and has no reason to be outlawed. Because, honestly - in the grand scheme of things (thanks OL) - your emotional well-being is worth as much as my toe nail clippings. The safety and longevity of the United States (or any) government won't be affected by a few less flags burned, and a few more people in jail.<br>
<br>
And just because your life is smooth sailing under your government, maybe there are people who are wronged. For complaining about protesters being 'misinformed', you sure are keeping a nice little double standard. There is no source of information more filtered than the general media - try and read a little more. What happened if you got what you wanted - no more protesters - and your government does something that affects you in a negative way? What do you do? You'd have no lawful way to argue your case. So much for 'demo'cracy.<br>
<br>
When people want warrants to be placed on suspected terrorists - I agree! If you don't need a warrant to arrest one group of people, this breach of constitution will eventually expand to encapsulate the general public - and then what? You can't trust the veil of virtue and good intention every government parades on their actions - not over human nature. People will be arrested on false charges because someone wanted it that way. It happens now...it would run rampant in the government you describe.<br>
<br>
So, be careful what you wish for. Because, some of these &quot;good for nothing little assholes&quot; that want the government to be freer than the people are getting what they want.<br>
